1
00:00:01,090 --> 00:00:02,890
Give you an inch
and you'll take a mile, huh?

2
00:00:02,890 --> 00:00:04,090
You're no different.

3
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:06,860
You always looked annoyed by me back then.

4
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:07,850
How rude.

5
00:00:07,870 --> 00:00:10,620
You are a nuisance.
And you keep provoking me at every turn.

6
00:00:10,620 --> 00:00:12,410
-Fine, let's compete.
-You're so clingy.

7
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:15,050
Let's see which of us is
better suited to be his rival.

8
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:16,590
His rival...

9
00:00:16,610 --> 00:00:17,540
It's you, right?

10
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:19,520
For now, maybe.

11
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:21,950
But if I become
the top salesman in Section 2,

12
00:00:21,950 --> 00:00:24,450
he'll notice me, won't he?

13
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:27,230
Do you really think
I'll let you have first place?

14
00:00:28,180 --> 00:00:30,160
Don't underestimate me.

15
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:31,610
Understood.

16
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:34,750
Since you've put it that way, I'll accept

17
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:36,340
your challenge.

18
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:38,870
[Fake Fact Lips]

19
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:44,210
[Episode 8: What can I say? Geez...]

20
00:01:42,910 --> 00:01:43,860
Good work.

21
00:01:43,979 --> 00:01:45,310
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

22
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:53,620
Whoa.

23
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,420
Working overtime?

24
00:01:56,110 --> 00:01:57,710
Thank you for your hard work.

25
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,120
You're so slow.

26
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:05,860
Even an honor student would be speechless.

27
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:08,240
Unlike you,
I'm not wasting time for no reason

28
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,440
when I work overtime.

29
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:13,230
I just have some work
that I want to finish today.

30
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:15,670
I'm not gonna lose to you.

31
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,490
Don't just talk. Get to work.

32
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,390
I am working.

33
00:02:19,770 --> 00:02:21,600
I'm practically getting tendonitis.

34
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,540
So annoying.

35
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,040
Are you here just to mess with me?

36
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:25,900
Just checking what you're doing.

37
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,820
I wouldn't do anything so petty
to my rival.

38
00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:31,940
Even though I accepted your challenge,
I don't see you as my rival.

39
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:33,230
You've got nerve saying that.

40
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:35,960
You can only keep up that calm expression
for now.

41
00:02:36,370 --> 00:02:37,400
I feel

42
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:39,280
things have been tense lately

43
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:41,160
between Mr. Shido and Mr. Futami.

44
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:42,950
Did they have a falling out?

45
00:02:42,950 --> 00:02:43,900
You didn't know?

46
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,880
Those two are competing
against each other.

47
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:46,790
Huh? Why?

48
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:48,300
What about his competition
with Mr. Yotsuya?

49
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:49,570
Who knows.

50
00:02:49,590 --> 00:02:52,400
But Mr. Futami is really excellent too.

51
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:54,730
Ah.

52
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,579
I heard Mr. Futami.

53
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,510
landed the contract for the Arphed system.

54
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:02,360
It seems he quickly won over
that difficult person in charge.

55
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:05,910
Hah, the social skills of people
from Western Japan are truly impressive.

56
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:06,790
Good work today.

57
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:07,760
Ah, Mr. Yotsuya.

58
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:09,040
Where is Shido?

59
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:11,080
Over there, going at it.

60
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:14,020
So noisy. I can't focus at all.

61
00:03:14,050 --> 00:03:15,430
You're the louder one.

62
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:16,210
No, you are.

63
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:16,850
What are you talking about?

64
00:03:16,850 --> 00:03:18,829
Mr. Yotsuya, are you leaving now?

65
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,140
Ah.

66
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:25,670
Ah.

67
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:29,060
I'm busy with the contract
you failed to get,

68
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:32,840
the Monclaire deal.
I'm very busy now.

69
00:03:32,870 --> 00:03:35,790
It's just your first contract
since you transferred here.

70
00:03:35,790 --> 00:03:37,730
Is there a need to be so excited?

71
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:41,760
This is the glorious first step
toward becoming the top in Section 2.

72
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:44,290
Hey, you two, that's enough.

73
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,910
-So annoying.
-So annoying.

74
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,540
It's none of your business.

75
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:51,250
Sorry, Yotsuya.

76
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,800
This is a competition
between me and this guy.

77
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:57,800
Hey.

78
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:23,010
Ryo.

79
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:30,790
Zen.

80
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,200
Sorry about earlier.

81
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,490
What's up?

82
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,400
No, it's just...

83
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,310
The trip we talked about.

84
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:52,050
The one for your birthday.

85
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,330
Ah.

86
00:04:54,130 --> 00:04:55,790
Things like accommodations…

87
00:04:56,060 --> 00:04:58,520
If we don't book them soon,
it'll be too late.

88
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,700
If you're okay with it,

89
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:05,290
I'll

90
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:06,810
arrange everything.

91
00:05:07,530 --> 00:05:10,330
-No, leaving it all to you is too…
-No, no.

92
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,040
I actually

93
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:13,370
enjoy doing this kind of planning.

94
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,480
Really?

95
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:18,130
Then, can I leave it to you?

96
00:05:18,130 --> 00:05:18,730
Of course.

97
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:22,810
You're very busy.

98
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,520
So are you.

99
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:26,760
But

100
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:29,540
I can't lose to Futami.

101
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:33,570
Though he acts like that,
he's really capable at work.

102
00:05:35,690 --> 00:05:37,350
You two really are competing?

103
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:38,740
Competing?

104
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:42,390
No, he's the one who started provoking me.

105
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:47,220
Then

106
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:49,990
why don't you just back down?

107
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:51,730
Huh?

108
00:05:53,530 --> 00:05:55,730
Why do you have to push yourself so hard?

109
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:02,590
I'm more suitable for Yotsuya
than you are.

110
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:05,030
No.

111
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:08,530
Shido.

112
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:14,130
I, the excellent one,
am heading back now.

113
00:06:17,530 --> 00:06:19,130
I'll go back to work then.

114
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,120
Wait a minute.

115
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,650
Futami.

116
00:06:38,370 --> 00:06:39,400
Well...

117
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,240
Yeah?

118
00:06:41,420 --> 00:06:43,440
About your competition with Shido...

119
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,210
Well...

120
00:06:46,159 --> 00:06:47,620
How about I take his place?

121
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,370
Hah?

122
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:49,710
So,

123
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:52,140
I want you to compete with me
instead of Shido.

124
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:52,940
No.

125
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,100
Why?

126
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:57,290
If I don't surpass Shido first,

127
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,010
you'll also find it boring, right?

128
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:01,100
No, I won't...

129
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,170
Besides,

130
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:04,150
I've got a wager riding on this.

131
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:06,260
What is it?

132
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,380
That's a secret.

133
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:08,940
Ah.

134
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:12,680
By the way, I'm going on a business trip
starting tomorrow.

135
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,740
With Shido.

136
00:07:13,770 --> 00:07:14,720
Hah?

137
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,600
Why haven't I heard about that?

138
00:07:17,810 --> 00:07:19,460
Of course you haven't.

139
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:22,010
You and I are not in the same department.

140
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,420
Whatever.

141
00:07:24,590 --> 00:07:27,250
I'll make sure

142
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,800
to leave a deep mark.

143
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:38,820
What can I say?

144
00:07:43,670 --> 00:07:44,440
Geez.

145
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:08,800
I don't feel right
about handing the project over to you.

146
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:10,380
Don't worry.

147
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:12,880
I'll do a better job than you.

148
00:08:13,890 --> 00:08:15,340
You're really confident.

149
00:08:15,340 --> 00:08:16,540
Same goes for you two.

150
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:19,140
What does "you two" mean?

151
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:21,050
Yotsuya, of course.

152
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:23,780
You bring him up
whenever you get the chance.

153
00:08:27,470 --> 00:08:28,380
Why are you

154
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,600
so obsessed with Yotsuya?

155
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:31,700
Hmm?

156
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,169
Are you interested?

157
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,039
No.

158
00:08:35,429 --> 00:08:36,549
Go on, ask me.

159
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:37,580
Forget it.

160
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:40,480
You're supposed to press further
at a time like this.

161
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,590
I've lost interest now.

162
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,300
Yotsuya...

163
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,020
Are you going to say it?

164
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,640
That guy

165
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,530
is someone special to me.

166
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,120
My family...

167
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,720
I don't get along well with them.

168
00:08:59,050 --> 00:09:00,840
I went against my parents

169
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:02,470
and chose my own path in life.

170
00:09:03,450 --> 00:09:03,890
Then,

171
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:05,800
I entered university.

172
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:07,120
And I met that guy.

173
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:11,220
Sometimes, I wonder
if I really chose the right path.

174
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,750
Once in a while, I feel lost.

175
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,420
I know how that feels.

176
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:17,590
Same here.

177
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,480
I don't get along well with my dad either.

178
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,560
Oh, really?

179
00:09:22,090 --> 00:09:23,640
He's quite strict.

180
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:25,130
Oh.

181
00:09:25,850 --> 00:09:27,180
I'm a little surprised.

182
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,100
I thought you wouldn't have such issues.

183
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,340
I've been through a lot,

184
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:35,210
but I'm fine now.

185
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:38,920
Did you two make up?

186
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,200
I realized

187
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,860
that was my life.

188
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:46,190
Yeah.

189
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:48,050
After that,

190
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:50,160
I made all my own decisions,

191
00:09:50,810 --> 00:09:52,630
no matter what my father said.

192
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:57,660
-Gradually, he just gave up.
-Yeah.

193
00:10:02,490 --> 00:10:03,180
I think

194
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:05,990
since it's a path you chose for yourself,

195
00:10:05,990 --> 00:10:07,720
you can be a bit more confident.

196
00:10:13,140 --> 00:10:14,280
Yeah.

197
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:16,920
Because

198
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:20,600
even if you meet
your father's expectations,

199
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:23,560
he won't meet yours.

200
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:27,780
Right.

201
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,170
Yeah.

202
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:33,580
Those words

203
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:35,860
hit me hard back then.

204
00:10:36,690 --> 00:10:38,290
It made me feel a lot lighter.

205
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,590
That's

206
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:43,530
why I really respect Yotsuya.

207
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:50,540
What's with that look?

208
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:52,910
Nothing.

209
00:10:53,860 --> 00:10:56,330
Sorry for interrupting your trip
down memory lane.

210
00:10:56,330 --> 00:10:59,590
I actually said those words
to Yotsuya back in high school.

211
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,520
Don't talk nonsense.

212
00:11:01,650 --> 00:11:03,030
How is that possible?

213
00:11:03,050 --> 00:11:06,050
If you don't believe me,
you can ask Yotsuya yourself.

214
00:11:10,060 --> 00:11:11,060
Does that mean...

215
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,190
all this time...

216
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,440
I've been saved by your words?

217
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:16,290
Hah.

218
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:17,810
You could say that.

219
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:21,090
How terrible.

220
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:23,040
However,

221
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:24,520
this just proves

222
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:26,900
you can't beat me.

223
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:27,950
No.

224
00:11:27,970 --> 00:11:30,430
Let's put that aside for now.

225
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:31,420
And then?

226
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:34,690
Who did you say
was more suitable for Yotsuya?

227
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:36,560
That was...

228
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:37,990
-And then...
-First of all,

229
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:40,480
a relationship
where two people suit each other

230
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:43,310
can't exist if they aren't equals, right?

231
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,150
From what you've told me,

232
00:11:45,190 --> 00:11:48,290
your admiration for Yotsuya
seems one-sided.

233
00:11:48,310 --> 00:11:49,680
Does that count as being equals?

234
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:50,300
No,

235
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:51,440
it doesn't

236
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:52,570
In other words,

237
00:11:52,590 --> 00:11:55,450
you aren't on equal footing
with Yotsuya right now.

238
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:17,180
[Aoba Traffic
Taxi]

239
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:20,960
Now you don't want to compete
with me anymore, do you?

240
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,780
Just come with me.

241
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:25,050
Quite the opposite.

242
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:28,680
I've become interested in you.

243
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:29,590
Eh?

244
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:33,380
I might want to get to know you better.

245
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:35,640
Stop joking. Let's go.

246
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,250
Hey.

247
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,450
Let's grab a drink tonight.

248
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,310
I've got a dinner appointment
with a client.

249
00:12:41,310 --> 00:12:42,620
We can do it after that.

250
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,170
You're so clingy.

251
00:12:44,460 --> 00:12:45,410
Oh, right.

252
00:12:45,630 --> 00:12:47,240
That's my strength.

253
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:48,430
I wouldn't know that.

254
00:12:48,430 --> 00:12:49,840
Well, now you know.
That's all that matters.

255
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,710
Why do I need to know?

256
00:12:51,730 --> 00:12:55,000
Hey, you…

257
00:12:57,170 --> 00:12:58,040
Well...

258
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,170
Hmm...

259
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:01,450
Let's have another contest.

260
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:03,260
About what?

261
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:05,670
About what? A proper rivalry.

262
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:11,190
Whoever gets promoted first wins.

263
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,070
Sure.

264
00:13:20,770 --> 00:13:21,510
I

265
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:24,670
seem to like people who make good rivals.

266
00:13:25,370 --> 00:13:25,970
Eh?

267
00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:27,740
So,

268
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:28,850
I'm sorry.

269
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,030
I don't want to be with you anymore.

270
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:36,890
Wait a minute...

271
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:58,810
So understandable...

272
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:00,620
I...

273
00:14:24,190 --> 00:14:25,310
Hey.

274
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:27,120
Sorry.

275
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:28,250
Did I wake you?

276
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:30,640
No, it's fine.

277
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,130
Your voice sounds a bit off.

278
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:35,280
I drank quite a bit.

279
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:37,840
I just got back to the hotel.

280
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:38,790
Is that so?

281
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:43,470
You must be exhausted working so late.

282
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:46,290
You had to entertain the client.

283
00:14:46,330 --> 00:14:47,790
There was a second round, right?

284
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:51,080
No. After the business dinner,
I went out for drinks with Futami.

285
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:51,640
Eh?

286
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:52,900
Huh?

287
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:56,990
He said
he'd send you photos of us drinking.

288
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:02,490
No, I didn't get them.

289
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,330
Maybe he went back to his room
and fell asleep.

290
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,220
Speaking of which,

291
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,840
you told Futami what I said to you, right?

292
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,010
Eh?

293
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:15,190
You know, "even if you meet
your parents' expectations,

294
00:15:15,190 --> 00:15:16,890
they won't meet yours."

295
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:19,100
Ah... Eh...

296
00:15:19,590 --> 00:15:22,230
Did Futami tell you about that?

297
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,350
Ah, wait, how embarrassing.

298
00:15:25,370 --> 00:15:27,710
He said your words really hit him.

299
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:29,440
He was bragging to me about it.

300
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:31,910
Eh? Really?

301
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,830
You two are surprisingly

302
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,620
similar.

303
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:37,450
When I talk to Futami,

304
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:39,240
it reminds me of the old days

305
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:42,150
when you and I were just ordinary rivals.

306
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:49,870
I sent you the hotel details.

307
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:52,180
Did you check them?

308
00:15:52,510 --> 00:15:53,960
Ah, yes.

309
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:55,450
Thank you.

310
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:58,400
You're welcome.

311
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:00,970
I'm researching restaurants now.

312
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,530
I'll make sure you have a good time.

313
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:05,830
Don't push yourself too hard.

314
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,310
You're busy too.

315
00:16:08,370 --> 00:16:09,450
Besides,

316
00:16:10,350 --> 00:16:12,330
just being able
to spend some quiet time with you

317
00:16:12,330 --> 00:16:13,360
is enough for me.

318
00:16:14,010 --> 00:16:14,580
Yeah.

319
00:16:17,340 --> 00:16:19,170
I'm really looking forward to it.

320
00:16:19,170 --> 00:16:19,780
Yeah.

321
00:16:20,830 --> 00:16:22,170
Hey, Zen.

322
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,510
I really want to see you.

323
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,140
Alright, alright.

324
00:16:29,810 --> 00:16:31,920
I have to get up early tomorrow,
so I'm going to sleep.

325
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:33,580
You should get some sleep too.

326
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:34,680
Yeah.

327
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:37,820
Good night.

328
00:16:39,710 --> 00:16:40,450
Good night.

329
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:05,380
I want to see you too.

330
00:17:07,730 --> 00:17:10,490
Why couldn't I just say it?

331
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:18,770
Ah.

332
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:20,839
Hey.

333
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,130
Even though the business trip is over,

334
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:27,010
being back in Tokyo
doesn't really feel like coming home.

335
00:17:27,020 --> 00:17:29,220
I'm heading straight home then.

336
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:30,360
Oh, really?

337
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:32,920
Let's go get something to eat.

338
00:17:33,070 --> 00:17:34,560
No, I have somewhere to go.

339
00:17:34,590 --> 00:17:35,720
Where are you going?

340
00:17:35,730 --> 00:17:36,740
I can go anywhere I want, can't I?

341
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:38,440
Come on, tell me.

342
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:42,030
I'm trying
to find out more about you, Shido.

343
00:17:42,060 --> 00:17:43,870
You're so annoying.

344
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:46,380
Just going to buy something.

345
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:47,380
Buy what?

346
00:17:49,410 --> 00:17:50,920
A little gift for someone

347
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,210
who has always looked after me.

348
00:17:53,630 --> 00:17:54,440
Hah.

349
00:17:55,230 --> 00:17:57,380
You've got a surprisingly cute side.

350
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:58,020
Hah.

351
00:17:58,650 --> 00:17:59,810
Alright.

352
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:01,430
I'll go with you

353
00:18:01,450 --> 00:18:02,760
to choose the gift.

354
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:03,580
No need.

355
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:05,190
Don't follow me.

356
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:09,260
I'm following you anyway.

357
00:18:10,830 --> 00:18:11,350
Yeah.

358
00:18:13,430 --> 00:18:16,560
[Already in Tokyo?]

359
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:19,260
[Want to have dinner together later?]

360
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:22,210
[Sorry, still working.]

361
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:33,230
Thanks for your hard work.

362
00:18:33,230 --> 00:18:34,930
Yeah, same to you.

363
00:18:36,380 --> 00:18:39,990
Today's negotiation was really tough.

364
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:42,800
Go home and get some rest early.

365
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:44,040
Okay.

366
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:46,140
What about you, Mr. Yotsuya?

367
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:48,880
I'll wrap up a few things
before heading back.

368
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:50,920
Don't push yourself too hard.

369
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,040
You look a little pale.

370
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:54,210
I'm fine.

371
00:18:55,770 --> 00:18:59,080
Once I get through this, there's something
to look forward to on the weekend.

372
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:00,390
Oh, that's nice.

373
00:19:00,420 --> 00:19:01,480
Your girlfriend?

374
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,260
Who knows.

375
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,130
Alright, hurry back.

376
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:06,710
Then I won't hesitate.

377
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:08,090
I'm leaving now.

378
00:19:40,420 --> 00:19:41,690
It's fine.

379
00:19:53,470 --> 00:19:54,670
Wait, is it for a guy?

380
00:19:55,290 --> 00:19:56,060
What?

381
00:19:57,490 --> 00:20:01,240
From the way you spoke, I thought
you were buying a gift for your lover.

382
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,300
It's not like that.

383
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,080
Hah.

384
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:06,420
How boring.

385
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,580
Then you can go back.

386
00:20:08,890 --> 00:20:09,750
No.

387
00:20:11,190 --> 00:20:13,620
I actually want a tie myself.

388
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:15,220
By the way,

389
00:20:15,950 --> 00:20:17,650
who is it really for?

390
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:20,090
No one in particular.

391
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:21,400
Just a normal friend.

392
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:22,880
You have friends?

393
00:20:22,910 --> 00:20:23,800
How rude.

394
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:26,820
Fine.

395
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,990
Gifts are nice,

396
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,910
but words are better.

397
00:20:33,410 --> 00:20:34,230
When it comes down to it,

398
00:20:34,230 --> 00:20:36,200
directly conveying your feelings

399
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:37,760
is what truly moves people.

400
00:20:38,460 --> 00:20:41,460
You don't seem very good with words.
This is my advice.

401
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,930
If I could just say everything like you,
things would be so much easier.

402
00:20:44,930 --> 00:20:45,520
Oh.

403
00:20:46,740 --> 00:20:48,880
Oh? You're teasing me, aren't you?

404
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:18,720
[Sorry, still working.]

405
00:21:20,270 --> 00:21:21,430
Is it work?

406
00:21:23,650 --> 00:21:24,790
It's not.

407
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,100
Sorry, I'd like to get out of the car.

408
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:34,900
I'll be right back.

409
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:35,460
Could you

410
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:36,940
wait for me a moment?

411
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,390
I'll leave my bag here.

412
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:40,180
Sorry.

413
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,030
Zen.

414
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:46,850
Ryo.

415
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:48,140
You...

416
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,220
Why are you here?

417
00:21:51,230 --> 00:21:52,750
Are you going home?

418
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:53,440
Eh?

419
00:21:54,660 --> 00:21:55,930
Ah, yeah.

420
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:57,540
Well then…

421
00:21:58,670 --> 00:22:00,650
Come stay at my place tonight.

422
00:22:00,870 --> 00:22:01,920
Now?

423
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:03,970
No, but...

424
00:22:06,150 --> 00:22:06,880
Is that okay?

425
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,480
I have a taxi waiting.

426
00:22:29,730 --> 00:22:30,940
Sorry.

427
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:32,760
I forced you to come.

428
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:34,830
Eh?

429
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:36,430
Ah, no.

430
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:37,960
That's fine.

431
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:50,360
The business trip went well.

432
00:22:52,050 --> 00:22:54,380
The handover to Futami went smoothly too.

433
00:22:56,310 --> 00:22:57,190
Is that so?

434
00:22:58,630 --> 00:22:59,450
That's great.

435
00:23:04,910 --> 00:23:07,170
I'll catch some sleep before we get home.

436
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:10,020
Yeah, okay.

437
00:23:46,820 --> 00:23:47,870
Zen.

438
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:52,940
Stay over tonight.

439
00:24:57,510 --> 00:25:00,900
[In the Next Episode]

440
00:24:58,620 --> 00:25:00,750
Is there anything you want to say to me?

441
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:04,320
[Final Episode: It's a Full Moon]

442
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,780
Compared to not being able to see you,

443
00:25:04,820 --> 00:25:06,910
what I hate more
is not being needed by you.

444
00:25:06,910 --> 00:25:08,260
I'm really sorry.

445
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,610
What's going on between you two?

446
00:25:09,610 --> 00:25:11,530
Now you've ruined it.

447
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:13,610
Right now, we're not equals.

448
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:14,470
Hah?

449
00:25:14,490 --> 00:25:16,080
Just say what's on your mind.
